--> How I Went About It
Set up a simple crude feed (approximate composition).
Modeled an atmospheric distillation column as the first step.

Defined key inputs:
Feed flow & temperature
Number of stages
Reflux ratio
Condenser & reboiler setup

Ran simulations, observed outputs, and tweaked variables to see what happens.

--> What was Figured Out
Could separate crude into approximate fractions (yay!)
Learned how sensitive yields are to reflux, temperature, and stage numbers.
Generated a first-cut PFD with main streams and product fractions.
Got a feeling for energy requirements and column behavior.

---> Experiments Tweaks 
